    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear offensive ceiling, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (87.42), who remains our premier start. Facing Lorenzen in a favorable park environment, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a +14% park factor and optimal lineup positioning, making him a cornerstone for production. We are also heavily invested in the speed-first profile of our leadoff hitters; **Colt Keith** (69.64) and **Trea Turner** (69.86) provide essential stability. **Colt Keith** sees a significant boost from his lead-off spot and a favorable matchup against Ober, while **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (71.81) emerges as our highest-scoring outfielder today, buoyed by a +14% platoon edge against Boyle. These plays are critical in our strategy to maximize stolen base efficiency, our scarcest category.\n\nStrategic rotation decisions remain tight, particularly at the margins. **Caleb Durbin** (65.57) forced his way into the lineup despite the wind-in risk at his venue, purely due to the overwhelming +19% advantage against Drohan\u2019s high xERA of 10.13. The most difficult bench decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion** (42.21), who was bypassed despite a serviceable profile. Ultimately, the projection model opted for the higher efficiency of our bottom-tier starters like **Carson Benge** (46.03), who carries a more favorable platoon outlook. We are monitoring **Christian Yelich** (54.08) closely; while his talent profile is elite, the combination of a tough outing against Gray and wind-in concerns makes him a mid-tier play today. Managers should note that while **Kazuma Okamoto** (42.45) is starting, he faces a significant hurdle against the elite arm of Ohtani (2.67 xERA), which has suppressed his projection relative to his usual output.",
